Key Match Events: Trent Alexander-Arnold scored the decisive penalty to give England an emotional shootout victory over Switzerland.
Bukayo Saka scored for England in the 80th minute.
Breel Embolo scored for Switzerland in the 75th minute.
England advanced to the semifinals with a 5-3 win on penalties.
Post-Match Reflections: England reached their third semifinal in four tournaments.
Trent Alexander-Arnold's penalty was a significant moment in the match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at Merkur Spiel-Arena in Düsseldorf, Germany.
The match was covered by FOX.
